  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Leave no child behind: Improving Early Childhood Development in Malawi</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Malawian children with disabilities are often hidden away from public life and rarely get an education. Access to education is made worse by a lack of knowledge about children with disabilities, teachers lacking the capacity to teach children with disabilities, and an inappropriate school environment. This project works with several local and international partners in Malawi to support families as they enrol their children in early childhood education, and to build an approach to inclusive education into the training provided to early childhood teachers. The quality of inclusive education offered is improved, and more links are built between early education and primary schools. This work improves participants&#x2019; ability to continue throughout the education system. By working with schools, communities and government, this project offers an affordable model so the work can continue into the future.</narrative>
  </description>
